<subSubSection id="C35C654DFF80232CFF2BFB0CFD319FA1" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BF936C6FF80232CFF2BFB0CFDB59D43" blockId="5.[159,762,1207,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225">
The 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D45FF80232CFF60FB0CFEE19CF3" authorityName="P.Kramer" authorityYear="1877" box="[212,377,1207,1231]" class="Arachnida" family="Tarsonemidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Tarsonemidae</taxonomicName>
recorded from citrus are mostly mycophagous and only the broad mite, or citrus silver mite, 
<taxonomicName id="4C464D45FF80232CFE99FB45FD239D2A" authority="(Banks)" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[301,699,1278,1302]" class="Arachnida" family="Tarsonemidae" genus="Polyphagotarsonemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latus">
<emphasis id="B932EAD4FF80232CFE99FB45FDCF9D2A" box="[301,599,1278,1302]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="225">Polyphagotarsonemus latus</emphasis>
(Banks)
</taxonomicName>
, produces severe injury to citrus and other cultivated plants (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFF43FAFFFE439D60" author="Jeppson L. R. &amp; Keifer H. H. &amp; Baker E. W." box="[247,475,1348,1372]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" refId="ref13567" refString="Jeppson L. R., Keifer H. H., Baker E. W. 1975 - Mites injurious to economic plants - Berkeley: University California Press. pp. 614." type="book" year="1975">
Jeppson 
<emphasis id="B932EAD4FF80232CFEEBFAFFFE159D60" box="[351,397,1348,1372]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="225">et al</emphasis>
., 1975
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFE5CFAFFFD1C9D60" author="Gerson U." box="[488,644,1348,1372]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" pagination="163 - 178" refId="ref12690" refString="Gerson U. 1992 - Biology and control of the broad mite, Polyphagotarsonemus latus (Banks) (Acari: Tarsonemidae) - Exp. Appl. Acarol., 13: 163 - 178." type="journal article" year="1992">Gerson, 1992</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFD25FAFFFEEC9D43" author="Nucifora A. &amp; Vacante V." pageId="5" pageNumber="225" pagination="49 - 67" refId="ref15342" refString="Nucifora A., Vacante V. 2004 - Citrus mites in Italy. VII. The family Tarsonemidae. Species collected and notes on ecology - Acarologia, 44: 49 - 67." type="journal article" year="2004">Nucifora and Vacante, 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFECAFADCFDB99D43" author="Vacante V." box="[382,545,1383,1407]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" refId="ref17129" refString="Vacante V. 2010 - Citrus Mites - Wallingford: CABI Publishing. pp. 378." type="book" year="2010">Vacante, 2010</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF936C6FF80232CFF71FA22FD319FA1" blockId="5.[159,762,1207,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225">
<taxonomicName id="4C464D45FF80232CFF71FA22FDB89D8D" baseAuthorityName="Banks" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[197,544,1433,1457]" class="Arachnida" family="Tarsonemidae" genus="Polyphagotarsonemus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latus">
<emphasis id="B932EAD4FF80232CFF71FA22FDB89D8D" bold="true" box="[197,544,1433,1457]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="225">Polyphagotarsonemus latus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
probably represents a complex species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFE7AFA06FD119DE9" author="Lindquist E. E." box="[462,649,1469,1493]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" pagination="517" refId="ref14074" refString="Lindquist E. E. 1986 - The world genera of Tarsonemidae (Acari: Heterostigmata): a morphological, phylogenetic, and systematic revision, with a reclassification of family-group taxa in the Heterostigmata - Mem. Entomol. Soc. Can., 136, pp. 517." type="journal article" year="1986">Lindquist, 1986</bibRefCitation>
) and has a worldwide geographical distribution. Optimum development requires tropical climatic conditions and occurs at 25Â°C and at near saturation humidities (90-100% RH) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFECEF9F2FD1E9E5D" author="Jones V. P. &amp; Brown R. D." box="[378,646,1609,1633]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" pagination="466 - 469" refId="ref13602" refString="Jones V. P., Brown R. D. 1983 - Reproductive responses of the broad mite, Polyphagotarsonemus latus (Banks) (Acari: Tarsonemidae) to constant temperaturehumidity regimes - Ann. Entomol. Soc. Am., 76: 466 - 469." type="journal article" year="1983">Jones and Brown, 1983</bibRefCitation>
). The natural enemies of the citrus silver mite include fungi (
<taxonomicName id="4C464D45FF80232CFF12F934FEC49E9B" box="[166,348,1679,1703]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Clavicipitaceae</taxonomicName>
, Ascomycota) and mites (
<taxonomicName id="4C464D45FF80232CFD3EF934FF4C9EF6" authorityName="A.Berlese" authorityYear="1916" class="Arachnida" family="Phytoseiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Phytoseiidae</taxonomicName>
), and although positive results were reported with fungal pathogens and Phytoseiids, control of the citrus silver mite is commonly based on chemicals (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFF50F8A0FE139F0F" author="Vacante V." box="[228,395,1819,1843]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" pagination="331 - 342" refId="ref17084" refString="Vacante V. 2009 - Gli acari fitofagi degli agrumi - In: Vacante V., Calabrese F. (Eds). Citrus, Trattato di agrumicoltura. Bologna: Il sole 24 Ore Editoria specializzata. pp. 331 - 342." type="book chapter" year="2009">Vacante, 2009</bibRefCitation>
). The most important innovations concern studies on the economic injury level (EIL) and on methods of sampling and monitoring of populations (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFEE3F83EFE409FA1" author="Peaea J. E." box="[343,472,1925,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" pagination="2008 - 2015" refId="ref15706" refString="Peaea J. E. 1990 - Relationships of broad mite (Acari: Tarsonemidae) density to lime damage - J. Econ. Entomol., 83: 2008 - 2015." type="journal article" year="1990">Peaea, 1990</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD74B37FF80232CFE57F83EFD069FA1" author="Peaea J. E. &amp; Sharp J. L. &amp; Wysoki M." box="[483,670,1924,1949]" pageId="5" pageNumber="225" refId="ref15740" refString="Peaea J. E., Sharp J. L., Wysoki M. 2002 - Tropical Fruit Pests and Pollinators. Biology, Economic Importance, Natural Enemies and Control - Wallingford: CAB International. pp. 448." type="book" year="2002">
Peaea 
<emphasis id="B932EAD4FF80232CFD97F83EFDC89FA0" box="[547,592,1924,1948]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="225">et al</emphasis>
., 2002
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
